"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Plan: Add zstd Compression to JSONL Transcript Storage\n\n## Context\n\nJSONL transcript files account for 97.7% of git object size (4.3 GB / 1,062 files). On-disk, the repo goes from 4 MB to 419 MB with checkpoints. The biggest pain: `git push` of `entire/checkpoints/v1` takes 10-20s because git must transfer large uncompressed blobs. JSONL is highly redundant (~90% structural repetition), achieving 10-15x compression with zstd.\n\n**Goal:** Compress JSONL transcripts with zstd before storing as git blobs, reducing object sizes 10-15x. Add a migration command so existing users see immediate improvement.\n\n## Approach\n\n- Compress after redaction, before blob creation; decompress after blob read, before consumption\n- Content hash remains on pre-compression (redacted) data for dedup consistency\n- Compressed files use `.zst` suffix (e.g., `full.jsonl.zst`)\n- Read paths check for `.zst` first, fall back to uncompressed (backward compat)\n- `github.com/klauspost/compress` v1.17.11 is already an indirect dependency (promote to direct)\n- **Migration command** (`entire optimize`) rewrites the metadata branch tree to compress existing data\n- **Benchmarks** prove the improvement with simulated realistic workloads\n\n## Key Design Decisions\n\n1. **Compress before chunking** — zstd reduces 24 MB → ~2 MB, so most transcripts fit in one blob. Compressed chunks use raw byte splitting (no JSONL line-boundary awareness needed).\n\n2. **Migration for existing data** — `entire optimize` rewrites the `entire/checkpoints/v1` HEAD tree, replacing all `full.jsonl*` blobs with compressed `full.jsonl.zst*` blobs. Uses `ApplyTreeChanges()` tree surgery for O(depth) performance.\n\n3. **Shadow branch transcripts also compressed** — `.entire/metadata/<session>/full.jsonl` files from disk are redacted, compressed, stored as `full.jsonl.zst` blobs.\n\n---\n\n## Part A: Compression Infrastructure\n\n### Step 1: Create `compression` package\n\n**New file:** `cmd/entire/cli/compression/zstd.go`\n\n```go\nfunc Compress(data []byte) ([]byte, error)    // zstd.SpeedDefault\nfunc Decompress(data []byte) ([]byte, error)  // zstd.NewReader\nfunc IsCompressedName(name string) bool       // strings.HasSuffix(name, \".zst\")\nfunc CompressedName(name string) string       // name + \".zst\"\n```\n\nUses `github.com/klauspost/compress/zstd`. Per-call encoder/decoder (thread-safe, no pooling needed initially).\n\n**New file:** `cmd/entire/cli/compression/zstd_test.go` — round-trip, empty data, large JSONL, concurrent, invalid data.\n\n### Step 2: Add path constants\n\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/paths/paths.go` (after line 28)\n\n```go\nTranscriptCompressedFileName = \"full.jsonl.zst\"\nCompressedSuffix             = \".zst\"\n```\n\n### Step 3: Add compressed chunking to `agent/chunking.go`\n\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/agent/chunking.go`\n\n- `ChunkCompressed(data []byte, maxSize int) [][]byte` — raw byte splitting at boundaries\n- `ReassembleCompressed(chunks [][]byte) []byte` — raw byte concatenation\n\nExisting `ChunkFileName`/`ParseChunkIndex`/`SortChunkFiles` work unchanged with new base name.\n\n### Step 4: Modify `writeTranscript()` — metadata branch writes\n\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/committed.go:561` (the `writeTranscript` function)\n\nCurrent flow: Redact → content hash → ChunkTranscript → CreateBlobFromContent\nNew flow: Redact → content hash (unchanged on redacted data) → **Compress** → **ChunkCompressed** → CreateBlobFromContent with `full.jsonl.zst` filename\n\nKey change: Move content hash computation BEFORE compression (line 602 area), then compress, then chunk compressed bytes.\n\n### Step 5: Modify `replaceTranscript()` — UpdateCommitted path\n\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/committed.go:1252` (the `replaceTranscript` function)\n\nSame compression flow as Step 4. Update cleanup loop (line 1253-1258) to delete entries matching BOTH `full.jsonl*` and `full.jsonl.zst*` patterns (backward compat during transition).\n\n### Step 6: Modify `readTranscriptFromTree()` — primary read path\n\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/committed.go:1525` (the `readTranscriptFromTree` function)\n\nAdd compressed detection BEFORE existing uncompressed logic:\n1. Scan tree entries for `full.jsonl.zst` and `full.jsonl.zst.001`, etc.\n2. If found: read chunks → `ReassembleCompressed` → `Decompress` → return\n3. Fall through to existing uncompressed logic (backward compat)\n\nThis single function covers both the committed read path AND `GetTranscriptFromCommit()` (shadow branch reads) since the latter delegates to `readTranscriptFromTree()` at line 573.\n\n### Step 7: Modify `GetTranscriptFromCommit()` fallback reads\n\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/temporary.go:579-596`\n\nThe main `readTranscriptFromTree()` call at line 573 is covered by Step 6. Update the direct file fallback reads (lines 580-596) to try `full.jsonl.zst` first before `full.jsonl`.\n\n### Step 8: Modify shadow branch task transcript writes\n\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/temporary.go:341-368` (`addTaskMetadataToTree`, final checkpoint path)\n\nThis function now uses `ApplyTreeChanges` (tree surgery). The transcript write section (lines 341-368) currently does:\n- `os.ReadFile(opts.TranscriptPath)` → `agent.ChunkTranscript` → `CreateBlobFromContent` with `paths.TranscriptFileName`\n\nChange to: read → `compression.Compress` → `agent.ChunkCompressed` → `CreateBlobFromContent` with `paths.TranscriptCompressedFileName`\n\n### Step 9: Modify filesystem directory walks for compression\n\n**Two functions** walk filesystem metadata dirs and create blobs:\n\n1. `addDirectoryToEntriesWithAbsPath()` — `temporary.go:868` (old pattern, entries map)\n2. `addDirectoryToChanges()` — `temporary.go:935` (new pattern, TreeChange slice)\n\nBoth call `createRedactedBlobFromFile()` (committed.go:1444). Instead of modifying the shared helper (which handles all file types), add a wrapper: when the walked file is `.jsonl`, compress the redacted content before blob creation, and store with `.zst` suffix in the tree path.\n\n### Step 10: Compress subagent transcripts\n\n**Write paths:**\n- `committed.go:245-268` (`writeFinalTaskCheckpoint`) — after redaction, compress subagent content, store as `agent-<id>.jsonl.zst`\n- `temporary.go:370-402` (`addTaskMetadataToTree` subagent section) — same for shadow branch\n\n**Read path:**\n- `strategy/common.go:1069-1111` (`getTaskTranscriptFromTree`) — try `agent-<id>.jsonl.zst` first, decompress, fall back to `.jsonl`\n\n### Step 11: Modify condensation shadow branch reads\n\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go:468-478`\n\nThe `extractSessionData()` function reads shadow branch transcripts via `tree.File(metadataDir + \"/\" + paths.TranscriptFileName)`. Add compressed-first detection: try `full.jsonl.zst` → `Decompress()`, fall back to `full.jsonl`.\n\nNote: The **live transcript path** (line 464, `os.ReadFile(liveTranscriptPath)`) reads from disk and is always uncompressed — no changes needed there.\n\n### Step 12: Promote dependency & tidy\n\n- `go.mod`: promote `github.com/klauspost/compress` from indirect to direct\n- `go mod tidy`\n\n---\n\n## Part B: Migration Command (`entire optimize`)\n\n### Step 13: Add `entire optimize` command\n\n**New file:** `cmd/entire/cli/commands/optimize.go`\n\n```\nentire optimize [--dry-run]\n```\n\n**Implementation using `ApplyTreeChanges` tree surgery** (NOT the old FlattenTree pattern):\n\n1. Get `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch ref and HEAD commit/tree\n2. Walk the tree recursively to identify uncompressed transcript blobs:\n   - `*/full.jsonl` (and `*.001`, `.002` chunks)\n   - `*/agent-*.jsonl`\n3. Build `[]TreeChange` slice: for each uncompressed blob, read → compress → create new compressed blob → add change (delete old path, insert new `.zst` path)\n4. `ApplyTreeChanges()` → create commit → update branch ref\n5. Report: N files compressed, before/after total size\n\n**Dry-run mode** (default): scan and report what would be compressed + estimated savings, without modifying anything.\n\n**Key reusable functions:**\n- `checkpoint.ApplyTreeChanges()` (parse_tree.go:197) — O(depth) tree surgery\n- `checkpoint.CreateBlobFromContent()` (committed.go) — blob creation\n- `compression.Compress()` / `compression.IsCompressedName()` — from Step 1\n\n**Registration:** Add to `root.go:74` alongside existing commands.\n\n---\n\n## Part C: Benchmarks\n\n### Step 14: Compression benchmarks\n\n**New file:** `cmd/entire/cli/compression/zstd_bench_test.go`\n\nBenchmark with realistic JSONL data at various sizes (1 KB, 100 KB, 1 MB, 10 MB, 25 MB):\n- `BenchmarkCompress` — measures throughput + ratio\n- `BenchmarkDecompress` — measures throughput\n\nGenerate realistic JSONL by repeating actual Claude Code transcript line patterns (with varied content fields). Report `b.ReportMetric` for compression ratio.\n\n### Step 15: End-to-end storage benchmarks\n\n**New file:** `cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/compression_bench_test.go`\n\nFollows the pattern from `parse_tree_bench_test.go`:\n- `BenchmarkWriteTranscript` — Compressed vs Uncompressed sub-benchmarks\n- `BenchmarkReadTranscript` — Read back compressed vs uncompressed\n- `BenchmarkSimulatedPushPayload` — N checkpoints (50, 100, 200), total blob size comparison\n\n### Step 16: Migration benchmark\n\n**Add to:** `cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/compression_bench_test.go`\n\n- `BenchmarkMigrateCheckpoints` — 100 uncompressed checkpoints, full migration via ApplyTreeChanges\n\n---\n\n## Part D: Tests\n\n### Step 17: Unit and integration tests\n\n1. **`compression/zstd_test.go`** — round-trip, empty, large JSONL, concurrent, invalid data\n2. **`agent/chunking_test.go`** — `ChunkCompressed`/`ReassembleCompressed` at various sizes\n3. **`checkpoint/committed_test.go`** — new tests:\n   - Write compressed transcript → read back correctly\n   - Write old uncompressed transcript → read back correctly (backward compat)\n   - `replaceTranscript` cleans up both compressed and uncompressed formats\n4. **`checkpoint/temporary_test.go`** — shadow branch compressed write/read\n5. **`commands/optimize_test.go`** — migration rewrites tree, handles already-compressed data, dry-run mode\n\n---\n\n## Files Summary\n\n| File | Changes |\n|------|---------|\n| **NEW** `cmd/entire/cli/compression/zstd.go` | Compress/Decompress helpers |\n| **NEW** `cmd/entire/cli/compression/zstd_test.go` | Unit tests |\n| **NEW** `cmd/entire/cli/compression/zstd_bench_test.go` | Compression benchmarks |\n| **NEW** `cmd/entire/cli/commands/optimize.go` | `entire optimize` command |\n| **NEW** `cmd/entire/cli/commands/optimize_test.go` | Migration tests |\n| **NEW** `cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/compression_bench_test.go` | End-to-end storage benchmarks |\n| `cmd/entire/cli/paths/paths.go` | Add `TranscriptCompressedFileName`, `CompressedSuffix` |\n| `cmd/entire/cli/agent/chunking.go` | Add `ChunkCompressed`, `ReassembleCompressed` |\n| `cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/committed.go` | `writeTranscript`, `replaceTranscript`, `readTranscriptFromTree`, `writeFinalTaskCheckpoint` |\n| `cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/temporary.go` | `GetTranscriptFromCommit`, `addTaskMetadataToTree`, `addDirectoryToEntriesWithAbsPath`, `addDirectoryToChanges` |\n| `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` | `extractSessionData` shadow branch fallback |\n| `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go` | `getTaskTranscriptFromTree` compressed read |\n| `cmd/entire/cli/root.go` | Register `optimize` command |\n| `go.mod` | Promote klauspost/compress to direct |\n\n## Key Functions to Reuse\n\n- `CreateBlobFromContent()` (committed.go) — stores compressed bytes as blob\n- `ChunkFileName()`/`ParseChunkIndex()`/`SortChunkFiles()` (chunking.go) — work with new base name\n- `createRedactedBlobFromFile()` (committed.go:1444) — basis for compressed variant\n- `ApplyTreeChanges()` (parse_tree.go:197) — O(depth) tree surgery for migration\n- `UpdateSubtree